<HL> Business Brief:
Caesars World Inc.</HL>
<DD> 10/20/87</DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO>
<IN> CAW
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN>
<TEXT>
   Martin T. Sosnoff, a New York investor, said he lowered his stake in Caesars World Inc. to 16% of the common shares outstanding. 

   In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Mr. Sosnoff said he sold 338,975 Caesars World common shares on Oct. 15 and Oct. 16 for $22.50 to $25.25 each. 
As a result of the sales, Mr. Sosnoff holds 3,878,700 common shares. 

   Caesars World is a Los Angeles-based concern with interests in casinos, hotels, resorts and real estate development. 

   According to the filing, Mr. Sosnoff may continue to lower his holdings in Caesars, or he may purchase additional shares. 

   Mr. Sosnoff continues to hold his Caesars World stock as an investment but reserves the right "to alter his intention at any time," although he has no plans to do so, the filing said. 
Caesars World declined to comment. 

